## Why This Is Asked

Tests online update handling, DAG shortest paths, and amortized analysis.

## Key Concepts

- DAG shortest paths via topological order
- Dynamic relaxations under decreasing edge weights
- Amortized analysis and worst-case bounds

## Code Example

```javascript
function updateShortestPaths(n, adj, dist, s, t, u, v, wOld, wNew){
  // assume we know wOld and wNew with a decrease; perform relaxation
  if(dist[u] + wNew < dist[v]){
    dist[v] = dist[u] + wNew;
    // push v to a queue and relax its outgoing edges
  }
  // ... full propagation would run until convergence
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you adapt for non-DAG graphs?
- How does update order affect performance in practice?
